get.description: The Search Destination Endpoint is designed to help you locate specific destinations within Indonesia based on search keywords. It provides detailed information about destinations, including their city and province. This feature is ideal for building applications like shipping calculators, e-commerce checkout systems, or any service that requires precise location-based data.  This guide explains how to utilize the endpoint, covering setup, request parameters, responses, and practical examples.

parameters.name: key
parameters.description: Every request to this endpoint must include a valid API key in the request header. Your API key is your unique identifier and ensures secure access to the service.

parameters.name: limit
parameters.description: Maximum number of results to return. Default: 10.

parameters.name: offset
parameters.description: The starting position for the results (for pagination). Default: 0.

message.example: Invalid Api key, key not found

get.description: The Search International Destination Endpoint is designed to simplify the process of finding international destinations based on a search keyword. This endpoint is particularly useful for businesses that operate across borders, such as e-commerce platforms, shipping companies, or logistics providers. By providing access to international destination data, the API ensures accurate and efficient processing of global shipping needs.

parameters.name: search
parameters.description: Keyword to search for an international destination.

parameters.name: limit
parameters.description: Maximum number of results to return. Default: 10.

parameters.name: offset
parameters.description: Starting position for the results, useful for pagination. Default: 0.

origin.description: The ID unique of postal code, sub district, or district for the origin location.

destination.description: The ID unique of postal code, sub district, or district for the destination location.

weight.description: The weight of the package in grams (e.g., 1000 for 1kg).

price.description: Filter for price sorting (lowest or highest). Default is lowest.
